(1138, 9, '2021-03-09 15:59:02', '2021-03-09 15:59:02', '<strong><u>Sr. Marketing Manager</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>About Us</strong>\r\n\r\nSimply Group is a family of companies sharing common values, interests, and practices to deliver energy-efficient residential and commercial solutions, so Canadians never have to sacrifice comfort or quality for essential services. With steady year-over-year growth and over $1.45 billion in rental assets, Simply Group is one of Canada\'s leaders in whole-home comfort. Our team of more than 400 employees takes an innovative approach to offer a comprehensive source of solutions that improve the status quo for ourselves, our communities, and our clients. We are committed to making things better for everyone and advancing the careers of all our employees.\r\n\r\nSimply Group serves customers across Canada through multiple brands. Our companies are divided into five categories: home comfort, lending, lighting, new construction, and green living. We are proud to be Great Place to Work-Certified for six straight years and winner of the 2019 Best Business of the Year award from the National CanadianSME Business Awards. Join us on our path to success! <a href=\"https://www.mysimplygroup.com\">https://www.mysimplygroup.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities</strong>\r\n\r\nWe’re looking for a highly skilled Sr. Marketing Manager to help us promote our offerings by identifying consumer insights to drive meaningful communications.  We need an energetic and intuitive marketer with a deep understanding of creative development. Adept in online and traditional marketing, and highly skilled in visual communications.\r\n\r\nAs the Sr. Marketing Manager, you will manage the graphic design and content development team to deliver engaging content that meets the expectations of our customers. You should be extremely creative, dedicated, and possess excellent written and verbal communication skills.  Our ideal candidate will have extensive agency experience working with creatives, and a comprehensive knowledge of branding. He/she will develop plans to help establish our brand, allocating resources to different projects and consulting on short-term and long-term department goals. The successful candidate will have the ability to lead a team of content developers and designers and will drive creativity and enthusiasm in others. If you’re a skilled Marketing strategist, able to inspire your team members, we’d like to meet you.\r\n\r\n<strong>Job Duties/Tasks</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Work with and manage the creative team to produce new ideas for company branding, promotional campaigns, and marketing communications.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create and implement tailored marketing plans for the different lines of business.</li>\r\n 	<li>Shape brand standards and create procedures to ensure all creative execution is brand appropriate.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure brand messaging is strong and consistent across all channels and marketing efforts (including events, email campaigns, web pages and promotional material).</li>\r\n 	<li>Manage the project initiation process across all brands and business units and drive the creative execution process.</li>\r\n 	<li>Manage end-to-end marketing deliverables – brief development, creative briefing, creative development, timing, budget.</li>\r\n 	<li>Evaluate trends, assess new data and keep up-to-date with the latest marketing techniques.</li>\r\n 	<li>Supervise the department\'s daily workflow, assign project workload, and monitor deadlines and budgets.</li>\r\n 	<li>Hold regular meetings with program directors to review pipeline, resolve challenges, and present possible solutions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Collaborate with the cross-functional business teams to uncover insights and opportunities to develop and implement marketing strategies.</li>\r\n 	<li>Set, monitor and report on team goals.</li>\r\n 	<li>Effectively manage a team of 3 by delivering sound creative and executional excellence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Requirements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Bachelor’s degree in marketing, advertising, or communications</li>\r\n 	<li>Successful track record in marketing roles and creating marketing campaigns</li>\r\n 	<li>Excellent leadership, communication, decision-making and organizing skills</li>\r\n 	<li>Analytical and creative thinking</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience with digital and print marketing, content marketing, and social media marketing</li>\r\n 	<li>Proven ability to plan and manage budgets</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Simply Group offers a competitive salary, performance bonus opportunities and participation in our group benefits program. All candidates will be considered; however only qualified candidates will be contacted. Simply Group is happy to provide accommodation through the recruitment and interview process, and beyond.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Senior Marketing Manager', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'senior-marketing-manager__trashed', '', '', '2021-03-10 19:37:26', '2021-03-10 19:37:26', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=job_postings&#038;p=1138', 0, 'job_postings', '', 0),
(1140, 2, '2021-03-10 00:02:51', '2021-03-10 00:02:51', 'Corporate philanthropy is a key component of our Simply Group values—we are committed to contributing to the health, growth, and sustainability of our communities and its people. One cause that we especially hold near and dear is supporting the young people in our community.\r\n\r\nIn 2020, Simply Group was extremely proud to partner with <a href=\"https://jack.org/Home\">Jack.org</a>, an initiative that trains and empowers young Canadians to lead the charge in revolutionizing mental across the country. Through various charity training programs, Jack.org brings together young leaders who work to identify strategies and break down barriers to positive mental health in their communities. They also provide resources to enable young people to better understand and educate themselves about their own mental health.\r\n\r\nWith support and contributions from our leadership, employees, and partners, Simply Group was able to raise $22,000 in just 19 days for Jack.org. All of the money was put toward helping 40,000 young people across Canada access vital mental health education and resources.\r\n\r\nThis charitable drive would not have been possible without the entire Simply Group family coming together as a community to support Jack.org’s mission. We can only hope that our contribution made a lasting impact, and we look forward to partnering with Jack.org again!\r\n\r\nTo learn more about Simply Group’s charitable initiatives, please visit <a href=\"https://www.mysimplycares.com/\">mysimplycares.com</a>.', 'Simply Group Raises Over $20,000 for Mental Health Initiatives', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'simply-group-raises-over-20000-for-mental-health-initiatives', '', '', '2021-03-10 00:02:51', '2021-03-10 00:02:51', '', 0, 'https://www.mysimplygreen.com/?post_type=press_release&#038;p=1140', 0, 'press_release', '', 0),
